These commands allows to use remotely a notebook on kubernetes 

* Step 1: kubernetes port forwarding
	kubectl port-forward ppl-pod 9999:8888

* Step 2: run jupyter notebook from kubernetes. You need to allow for root.
	e.g. /#bash.$ jupyter-notebook --allow-root
	This will give an adress such as: http://localhost:8888/?token=da4ba3d6e97aa494c215131bc3b6ba47316cbc4999cc3dd0

* Step 3: Open the local browser on the forwarded port
	e.g. http://localhost:9999

* Step 4:  
	Copy the token given in Step 2 (da4ba3d6e97aa494c215131bc3b6ba47316cbc4999cc3dd0) in order to access the remote jupyter notebook
	 
	
